{"lemma":"دَخَنُ","slug":"دَخَنُ","root":"د.خ.ن","root_slug":"د-خ-ن","root_link":"/words/roots/د-خ-ن","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":5,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n12290","n12291","n12292"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AF%D9%8E%D8%AE%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to smoke (emit smoke; for example of a chimney, a fire)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be smoky (to taste or smell of smoke, or filled with smoke)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be smoke-colored (of a pot, etc.)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be bad, to be corrupt (e.g. of one's character, mind or morals)","tags":["figuratively"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to smoke (tobacco, etc.)","examples":[{"text":"هَلْ يُمْكِنُنِي التَّدْخِين؟","english":"Can I smoke?"}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"smoke, damp"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"pearl millet"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Denominal verb of دُخَان (duḵān, “smoke”).\n\nBorrowed from Aramaic דּוֹחַן (doḥan, “millet”), from Akkadian 𒌅𒄴𒉡 (/⁠duḫnu; tuḫnu⁠/, “millet”), ultimately from a variation of Proto-Semitic *ṭaḥan-/*ṭaḥaḥ- (“to grind, to pound, to crush, to break down into pieces; especially of corn”), found in طَحَّ (ṭaḥḥa, “to scrape, to grate, to remove an outside surface, to make flakes or powder, to break down into pieces”). Doublet of طَحَنَ (ṭaḥana, “to grind, to mill”) and cognate with Classical Syriac ܕܽܘܚܢܴܐ (duḥnā, “millet”) and Hebrew דֹּחַן (doḥan, “millet”). There is no direct connection to Proto-Indo-European *dʰoHnéh₂ although a distant relation has been suggested."},"ipa":["/da.xa.na/","/da.xi.na/","/dax.xa.na/","/da.xan/","/duxn/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n12290","headword_ar":"دُخْنٌ","root":"dxn","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A well-known kind of grain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAwarosN","text_ar":"جَاوَرْسٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) [i. e.] the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jAwrs","text_ar":"جاورس"},{"kind":"text","text":": (JK, M, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain grain smaller than that, very smooth, cold, dry, and constipating:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a species of millet;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"holcus saccharatus"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"holcus dochna"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Forskål;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sorghum saccharatum"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Delile: and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"holcus spicatus"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.: and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"panicum miliaceum"},{"kind":"text","text":"of Linn.: (Delile's “ Flor. Aegypt. Illustr., ” no. 164: no. 57: and no. 79:)] n. un. with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"p","text_ar":"ة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a single grain thereof."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.)"}],"source_refs":["JK","M","K"]},{"entry_id":"n12291","headword_ar":"دَخَنٌ","root":"dxn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxina","text_ar":"دَخِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[q. v.]. (JK, Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,] (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"of conflict and faction, sedition, discord, or the like. (TA.) ―         -b3-  Hence also, i. e. from"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxanu Aln~aAri","text_ar":"دَخَنُ النَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~abiyxi","text_ar":"الطَّبِيخِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (TA,) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A state of alteration for the worse, of intellect,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of religion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the grounds of pretension to respect"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"honour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.) ―         -b4-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxaAnN","text_ar":"دُخَانٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K.) See this word in two places. ―         -b5-  [Hence,] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A duskiness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dinginess, inclining to blackness;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duxonapN","text_ar":"دُخْنَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (JK, S, K;) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the colour of smoke,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see 1, last signification but one,) or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the colour of iron:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) it is in a sheep, (S,) or a horse and similar beasts, or in a garment, (TA,) and in a sword: (S, A, TA:) in this last it means (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a blackness that appears in the broad side, by reason of its great brightness:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"diversified wavy marks, streaks,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"grain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"firinod","text_ar":"فِرِنْد"},{"kind":"text","text":",) of a sword. (K.) ―         -b6-  Also (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Rancour, malevolence, malice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"spite."},{"kind":"text","text":"(JK, K, TA.) ―         -b7-  And (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Badness, corruptness,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wickedness, of nature"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["TA","S","A"]},{"entry_id":"n12292","headword_ar":"دَخِنٌ","root":"dxn","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[applied to food, and to flesh-meat,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Infected with smoke:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daxina","text_ar":"دَخِنَ"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-  And hence,] applied to wine, or beverage, (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Altered for the worse in odour."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rajulN daxinu Alxuluqi","text_ar":"رَجُلٌ دَخِنُ الخُلُقِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, JK, S) (tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A man bad, corrupt,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wicked, in respect of nature,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disposition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Sh, JK, TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daAxinN","text_ar":"دَاخِنٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".]"}],"source_refs":["Sh","JK","S"]}]}}